title: Bennie Green (trombone(1960)TIME records) Sonny Clark
description:
There are two famous jazzmen named Bennie Green......this one played the 

somewhat cumbersome trombone....the other is a pianist who is still contributing


This quintet LP from 1960 is quite good IMO because of Sonny Clark who was also

with the TIME/BAINBRIDGE label at the time.  Sonny's LP COOL STRUTTIN (1958 Blue 

Note) actually deserves the overused term CLASSIC.


Tracks #2 and #5 are incorrectly titled on both the packaging and the CD. 

I've correctly titled them in capital letters so you can quickly see the changes

I've made.  Track 2 is obviously COOL STRUTTIN, not IT'S TIME.  Track #5

is not COOL STRUTTIN'....it is in fact another Clark original entitled BLUE

MINOR


At a younger age I tangled with the trombone myself....I know how bloody 

difficult it is to tame this beast
